main event: Two individuals observed two brilliant objects that appeared to flatten to an oval shape over Kensington, Maryland on September 27, 1954.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 35 minutes and was conducted through a screened window., Initial sighting of the object indicated it disappeared below the horizon in the west., Irregular motions of the objects were noted., The objects were described as having unusual color and movement not typically seen in that area of the sky., The sighting was confirmed by a second witness.
witness description: Civilian employees living in Washington D.C.
